import ml.wolfe.examples.TaggingExample._

val doc = TokenSplitter(SentenceSplitter(
"John Denver is a Songwriter. Denver has produced many records"))
val example = doc.tokens.map(_.word)

val words = example.distinct
val tags = Seq('O, 'B_LOC, 'I_LOC, 'B_PER, 'I_PER)

BratRenderer.bratIE(doc)

// Define the domains or inputs, outputs and parameters
val maxLength = 15
implicit val Words = words.toDom withOOV "[OOV]"
implicit val Tags = tags.toDom
implicit val Y = Seqs(Tags, 0, maxLength)
implicit val Weights = Vectors(dim = 1000)

implicit val index = new SimpleIndex() // For indexing Weights vectors

// Define a score function

val firstName = Set("John", "Jack")
val lastName = Set("Denver")
val location = Set("Denver", "Dallas")
val punct     = Set(",", ".", "?", ";")
def lowercase(w: Words.Value) = w.head.isLower

def model(w: Weights.Term, x: Seq[Words.Value])(y: Y.Term) = {
    sum(0 until x.length) { i => 
        (w dot feature('bias, y(i))) +
        (w dot feature('word, y(i) -> x(i).toConst)) +
        (w dot feature('firstName, I(firstName(x(i)).toConst), y(i))) +
        (w dot feature('lastName, I(lastName(x(i)).toConst), y(i))) +
        (w dot feature('location, I(location(x(i)).toConst), y(i)))
    } + sum(0 until x.length - 1) { i => 
        w dot feature('pair, y(i) -> y(i + 1))
    }
} subjectTo (y.length === x.length) // Require one tag per word

val wStar = preloadWeights()

// An tag sequence that is too long for the example
val longSequence = IndexedSeq.fill(100)('O)
model(Weights.Const(wStar), example)(Y.Const(longSequence)).eval()

["import ml.wolfe.examples.TaggingExample._

val doc = TokenSplitter(SentenceSplitter(
"John Denver is a Songwriter. Denver has produced many records"))
val example = doc.tokens.map(_.word)

val words = example.distinct
val tags = Seq('O, 'B_LOC, 'I_LOC, 'B_PER, 'I_PER)

BratRenderer.bratIE(doc)","// Define the domains or inputs, outputs and parameters
val maxLength = 15
implicit val Words = words.toDom withOOV "[OOV]"
implicit val Tags = tags.toDom
implicit val Y = Seqs(Tags, 0, maxLength)
implicit val Weights = Vectors(dim = 1000)

implicit val index = new SimpleIndex() // For indexing Weights vectors","// Define a score function

val firstName = Set("John", "Jack")
val lastName = Set("Denver")
val location = Set("Denver", "Dallas")
val punct     = Set(",", ".", "?", ";")
def lowercase(w: Words.Value) = w.head.isLower

def model(w: Weights.Term, x: Seq[Words.Value])(y: Y.Term) = {
    sum(0 until x.length) { i => 
        (w dot feature('bias, y(i))) +
        (w dot feature('word, y(i) -> x(i).toConst)) +
        (w dot feature('firstName, I(firstName(x(i)).toConst), y(i))) +
        (w dot feature('lastName, I(lastName(x(i)).toConst), y(i))) +
        (w dot feature('location, I(location(x(i)).toConst), y(i)))
    } + sum(0 until x.length - 1) { i => 
        w dot feature('pair, y(i) -> y(i + 1))
    }
} subjectTo (y.length === x.length) // Require one tag per word

val wStar = preloadWeights()

// An tag sequence that is too long for the example
val longSequence = IndexedSeq.fill(100)('O)
model(Weights.Const(wStar), example)(Y.Const(longSequence)).eval()","// A tag sequence of the correct length
val betterSequence = IndexedSeq.fill(11)('O)
model(Weights.Const(wStar), example)(Y.Const(betterSequence)).eval()","// Find the optimal tag sequence for this example, by maxProduct
implicit val maxProductParams = BPParameters(iterations = 1)

def predict(x: Seq[Words.Value]) = argmax(Y) {
    model(Weights.Const(wStar), x)
} by maxProduct
val result = predict(example).evalResult()
(doc withTags result).toTaggedText"]

val maxLength = 15
implicit val Words = words.toDom withOOV "[OOV]"
implicit val Tags = tags.toDom

val lastName = Set("Denver")
val location = Set("Denver", "Dallas")
val punct     = Set(",", ".", "?", ";")
def lowercase(w: Words.Value) = w.head.isLower

def model(w: Weights.Term, x: Seq[Words.Value])(y: Y.Term) = {
    sum(0 until x.length) { i => 
        (w dot feature('bias, y(i))) +
        (w dot feature('word, y(i) -> x(i).toConst)) +
        (w dot feature('firstName, I(firstName(x(i)).toConst), y(i))) +
        (w dot feature('lastName, I(lastName(x(i)).toConst), y(i))) +
        (w dot feature('location, I(location(x(i)).toConst), y(i)))
    } + sum(0 until x.length - 1) { i => 
        w dot feature('pair, y(i) -> y(i + 1))
    }
} subjectTo (y.length === x.length) // Require one tag per word

val wStar = preloadWeights()

// An tag sequence that is too long for the example
val longSequence = IndexedSeq.fill(100)('O)
model(Weights.Const(wStar), example)(Y.Const(longSequence)).eval()","// A tag sequence of the correct length

model(Weights.Const(wStar), example)(Y.Const(betterSequence)).eval()","// Find the optimal tag sequence for this example, by maxProduct
implicit val maxProductParams = BPParameters(iterations = 1)

def predict(x: Seq[Words.Value]) = argmax(Y) {

} by maxProduct
val result = predict(example).evalResult()
(doc withTags result).toTaggedText","// The factor graph which was used to perform inference
result.factorGraphs.head","// Build a new model with factors between matching words
def matchingPairs(x: Seq[Words.Value]) =
    for (j <- 0 until x.length; i <- 0 until j; if x(i) != "." && x(i) == x(j)) yield (i, j)
    
def skipModel(w: Weights.Term,x: Seq[Words.Value])(y: Y.Term) = {
    def matches = matchingPairs(x)
    model(w,x)(y) + 
    sum(0 until matches.length) { i => 
        w dot feature('match, y(matches(i)._1) -> y(matches(i)._2))
    }
}

def predict2(x: Seq[Words.Value]) = argmax(Y) {
    skipModel(Weights.Const(wStar), x)
} by maxProduct

val result2 = predict2(example).evalResult()
(doc withTags result2).toTaggedText"]
